COMMUNICATION: How to talk to other players and staff

IN-ROOM
  say <message>       Speak to everyone in the room.
  whisper <who> <msg> Private in-room message.
  emote <action>      Perform an action (visible to room).
  converse            Auto-say mode; everything you type is spoken.
                      Type ** to exit converse mode.

PLAYER-TO-PLAYER
  telepathy <who> <msg>  Psionic mind contact. Both players must be
                         online. Requires introduction first (see:
                         introduce). Costs ISP.
  radio <message>        Broadcast on your radio frequency (see:
                         radio). Other players tuned to the same
                         frequency hear you.

STAFF CONTACT
  tell <staff> <msg>  Send a private message to online wizard staff.
                      Mortals cannot tell other mortals; use telepathy
                      after introducing yourself.
  reply <msg>         Reply to the last tell you received.

GLOBAL
  ooc <message>       Out-of-character channel, visible to all online.

WIZARD STAFF ONLY
  newbie, cre, admin, gossip, and legacy guild lines (fighter, mage,
  etc.) are restricted to wizard staff. Mortals do not have these
  lines. See: channels, wiz.

INTRODUCTION SYSTEM
  introduce <player>  Introduce yourself to a player in the same room.
                      Both parties learn each other's names. Required
                      before telepathy or remote psionics can target
                      another player.

NOTES
  shout and yell are not available to players.
  Type 'help <command>' for details on any specific command.

SEE ALSO: say, whisper, telepathy, radio, tell, ooc, introduce,
channels
